{"id": 3568, "title": "Ticket #3568: Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR", "description": "<blockquote>\nInformation about a connection needs to be logged by CEDAR and/or exposed in CEDAR's API to higher layers. This is to enable the audit log required by OSG for the HTCondor-CE. This includes a unique identifier for each new connection and extensive security information.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3612\" title=\"Fix authenticated name reporting in CEDAR for GSI\">#3612</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nFix authenticated name reporting in CEDAR for GSI</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-24 11:34</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35536\">[35536]</a></span>: log the command being authenticated, not DC_AUTHENTICATE. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span>  (By Zach Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-23 17:26</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35525\">[35525]</a></span>: propagate the authentication methods attempted into the sock object <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span>  (By Zach Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-22 13:54</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35488\">[35488]</a></span>: Fix build failure when building without GSI. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-22 11:31</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35484\">[35484]</a></span>: when resuming a session, extract the method used and put it into the sock. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span>  (By Zach Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-22 11:14</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35483\">[35483]</a></span>: store the authenticated name (DN, or FQAN with VOMS) in the cached session and restore it when resuming a session. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span>  (By Zach Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-19 16:13</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35469\">[35469]</a></span>: Implement DaemonCore::InstallAuditingCallback. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-19 15:42</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35468\">[35468]</a></span>: added a function getFQAuthenticatedName() to expose VOMS attributes, and put those in the sock object <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span>  (By Zach Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-19 13:34</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35465\">[35465]</a></span>: add callback function callout for authorization <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span>  (By Zach Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-18 10:59</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35454\">[35454]</a></span>: Include unmapped auth name in schedd audit log function. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-18 10:58</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35453\">[35453]</a></span>: Make the unmapped authenticated name available in the Sock object. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span> The audit log wants to print this identity. One flaw to be fixed is that any VOMS extensions of a GSI credential aren't available to the audit log. Another flaw is that no authentication information is available in the Sock object\u00a0[...]\n (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-17 14:13</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35440\">[35440]</a></span>: Add function for logging basic connection info to audit log. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span> The information logged is incomplete, and nobody calls the function yet. That will require changes in CEDAR and daemon-core.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2013-Apr-09 17:09</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"chngview?cn=35365\">[35365]</a></span>: Assign a unique id to every Sock object. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"tktview?tn=3568\" title=\"Add and expose connection and security information in CEDAR\">#3568</a></span> Every new Sock object is now assigned a unique identifier (an integer), useable by the audit log to relate messages for a given connection. The identifier is retrieveable via the new method getUniqueId().  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "enhance", "last_change": "2013-May-07 15:18", "status": "resolved", "created": "2013-Apr-09 17:06", "fixed_version": "2013-Apr-09 17:06", "broken_version": "v070900", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "Libs", "assigned_to": "zmiller", "derived_from": "#3493", "creator": "jfrey", "rust": "", "customer_group": "osg", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}